  'stripe-nonprofit-discount',
  '{"en": "Getting Stripe Nonprofit Discount (Save 0.7%)", "es": "Obtener descuento sin fines de lucro de Stripe"}',
  '{"en": "Registered 501(c)(3) nonprofits can save 0.7% on every transaction through Stripe''s nonprofit pricing. Here''s how to get it.\n\n**The Savings:**\n- Standard Stripe Rate: 2.9% + $0.30 per transaction\n- Nonprofit Rate: 2.2% + $0.30 per transaction\n- YOU SAVE: 0.7% on every donation\n\n**Real Impact Examples:**\n- $1,000 monthly donations: Save $84/year\n- $5,000 monthly donations: Save $420/year\n- $10,000 monthly donations: Save $840/year\n- $25,000 monthly donations: Save $2,100/year\n\nWith Tektons Table''s 3.5% platform fee:\n- Standard total: 6.4% + $0.30 per transaction\n- Nonprofit total: 5.7% + $0.30 per transaction\n\n**Step-by-Step Application Process:**\n\n**STEP 1: Prepare Your Documents**\nBefore starting, gather:\n- IRS 501(c)(3) Determination Letter (PDF)\n- Organization''s EIN (Employer Identification Number)\n- Organization legal name (must match IRS records)\n- Physical address (not a P.O. box)\n- Organization website or social media\n- Bank account information\n\n**STEP 2: Create Your Stripe Account**\n1. From your Tektons Table dashboard, click \"Connect Stripe\"\n2. Click \"Create a Stripe Account\"\n3. Choose \"Nonprofit\" when asked about organization type\n4. Fill in organization details exactly as they appear on your 501(c)(3) letter\n\n**STEP 3: Complete Identity Verification**\n1. Provide your personal information (as the account administrator)\n2. Add your phone number for 2-factor authentication\n3. Verify your email address\n4. Set a secure password\n\n**STEP 4: Submit Nonprofit Documentation**\n1. In Stripe Dashboard, go to Settings → Business Settings\n2. Click \"Apply for nonprofit pricing\"\n3. Upload your IRS 501(c)(3) Determination Letter\n4. Confirm your EIN matches the letter\n5. Submit application\n\n**STEP 5: Wait for Approval**\n- Typical approval time: 1-3 business days\n- Stripe will email you with the decision\n- If approved, nonprofit rates apply automatically\n- If denied, you can reapply with corrected documents\n\n**STEP 6: Connect Your Bank Account**\n1. In Stripe Dashboard, go to Settings → Bank Accounts\n2. Add your organization''s bank account\n3. Verify with micro-deposits (takes 1-2 days)\n4. Confirm the deposit amounts in Stripe\n\n**Common Issues & Solutions:**\n\n**Issue: Document Rejected**\n- Ensure letter is from the IRS (not state)\n- Must be official determination letter, not a tax filing\n- Document must be clear and readable\n- Name on letter must exactly match Stripe account name\n\n**Issue: EIN Mismatch**\n- Double-check EIN from your IRS letter\n- Remove any dashes or spaces\n- Ensure you''re using organization EIN, not personal SSN\n\n**Issue: Can''t Find Determination Letter**\n- Contact IRS at (877) 829-5500\n- Request a copy through IRS Tax Exempt Organization Search\n- Or use Form 4506-A to request letter copy\n\n**Issue: Approval Taking Too Long**\n- Check spam folder for Stripe emails\n- Log into Stripe Dashboard to see application status\n- Contact Stripe support through their dashboard\n\n**After Approval:**\n✓ Nonprofit rates apply to ALL future transactions automatically\n✓ No monthly fees or hidden charges\n✓ Same great features as standard Stripe\n✓ You can start accepting donations immediately\n\n**Important Notes:**\n- Nonprofit pricing is for 501(c)(3) organizations only\n- Churches and religious organizations qualify\n- Must maintain 501(c)(3) status\n- Stripe may request updated documentation annually\n- Existing transactions at standard rate won''t be refunded\n\n**Need Help?**\nOur chatbot can walk you through each step. Just ask:\n- \"How do I apply for Stripe nonprofit discount?\"\n- \"What documents do I need for Stripe nonprofit pricing?\"\n- \"My Stripe nonprofit application was denied, what do I do?\"\n\n**Direct Stripe Resources:**\n- Stripe Nonprofit Pricing: stripe.com/nonprofits\n- Stripe Support: support.stripe.com\n- IRS EO Search: irs.gov/charities-and-nonprofits", "es": "Las organizaciones sin fines de lucro 501(c)(3) pueden ahorrar 0.7% en cada transacción..."}',
